        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 29 at 3:47PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 347 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles west of Marion, or near B.R. Parkway-Little Switzerland To
Linville, moving southwest at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
B.R. Parkway-Craggy To Little Switzerland and Busick.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
